		<div class="entries" data-archive="default" data-layout="grid" data-cards="boxed"><article class="entry-card card-content post-17939 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-tutorials tag-arduino tag-esp-idf tag-esp32 tag-esp32-p4 tag-espressif tag-freertos tag-microcontroller tag-platformio tag-vs-code tag-waveshare" data-reveal="bottom:no"><ul class="entry-meta" data-type="simple:slash" data-id="j0qilM" ><li class="meta-categories" data-type="pill"><a href="https://www.circuitstate.com/tutorials/" rel="tag" class="ct-term-18">Tutorials</a></li></ul><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.circuitstate.com/tutorials/getting-started-with-waveshare-esp32-p4-pico-microcontroller-development-board/" rel="bookmark">Getting Started with Waveshare ESP32-P4-Pico  Microcontroller Development Board</a></h2><a class="ct-media-container boundless-image" href="https://www.circuitstate.com/tutorials/getting-started-with-waveshare-esp32-p4-pico-microcontroller-development-board/" aria-label="Getting Started with Waveshare ESP32-P4-Pico  Microcontroller Development Board"><img width="768" height="576" src="https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-768x576.jpg" class="attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-post-image" alt="Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" srcset="https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-300x225.jpg 300w, https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-150x113.jpg 150w, https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-P4-Pico-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-1-1320x990.jpg 1320w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" style="aspect-ratio: 4/3;" title="Getting Started with Waveshare ESP32-P4-Pico Microcontroller Development Board 1"></a><div class="entry-excerpt"><p>Learn how to use the ESP32-P4-Pico high-performance microcontroller development board from Waveshare. Use Arduino, ESP IDF, PlatformIO and VS Code for software development.</p>
</div><ul class="entry-meta" data-type="simple:slash" data-id="kXJEVS" ><li class="meta-author"><a class="ct-meta-element-author" href="https://www.circuitstate.com/author/vishnumaiea/" title="Posts by Vishnu Mohanan" rel="author"><span>Vishnu Mohanan</span></a></li><li class="meta-date" ><time class="ct-meta-element-date" datetime="2026-03-08T15:37:24+05:30">8 March 2026</time></li></ul></article><article class="entry-card card-content post-17295 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-tutorials tag-arduino tag-ble tag-bluetooth tag-esp-idf tag-esp32 tag-esp32-s3 tag-espressif tag-freertos tag-iot tag-microcontroller tag-platformio tag-vs-code tag-waveshare tag-wi-fi" data-reveal="bottom:no"><ul class="entry-meta" data-type="simple:slash" data-id="j0qilM" ><li class="meta-categories" data-type="pill"><a href="https://www.circuitstate.com/tutorials/" rel="tag" class="ct-term-18">Tutorials</a></li></ul><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.circuitstate.com/tutorials/getting-started-with-waveshare-esp32-s3-zero-wi-fi-bluetooth-development-board/" rel="bookmark">Getting Started with Waveshare ESP32-S3-Zero  Wi-Fi &amp; Bluetooth Development Board</a></h2><a class="ct-media-container boundless-image" href="https://www.circuitstate.com/tutorials/getting-started-with-waveshare-esp32-s3-zero-wi-fi-bluetooth-development-board/" aria-label="Getting Started with Waveshare ESP32-S3-Zero  Wi-Fi &amp; Bluetooth Development Board"><img fetchpriority="high" width="768" height="576" src="https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-S3-Zero-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-Featured-Image-01-JPG-2-768x576.jpg" class="attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-post-image" alt="Getting Started with ESP32-S3-Zero CIRCUITSTATE Electronics Featured-Image" loading="lazy" decoding="async" srcset="https://www.circuitstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Getting-Started-with-ESP32-S3-Zero-CIRCUITSTATE-Electronics-F